<plot>The film is a 'visual recording' of the thoughts and memories of an elderly person on returning to the location of their birthplace and upbringing . The sole survivor of a once close and loving family, and the last in the genetic line. 'Yr Aelwyd' is a Welsh expression that has no direct English translation, but describes the feeling, memories, warmth and security of the home and family, and in this case the consequential nostalgia. The direct translation of Aelwyd means 'hearth' or 'fireplace', something that would be found in everyone's home in bygone days and would be the 'heart' and the feeling of 'home'.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?667754</url></doc>
